Hedley, an old-school country singer, songwriter and fiddler whose sound recalls Johnny Paycheck and Merle Haggard, has spent years paying his dues in Nashville.
Now it's time for the rest of the world to take notice.
Hedley has said that country music was perfected in 1965, a statement he admits "was a bit hyperbolic."
